The use of Descartes' rule of signs suggests a connection to real algebraic geometry (cs.SC) and the study of roots of polynomials. Finally, the mention of "sparse polynomials with sparse coefficients" suggests a connection to the study of sparse graphs and combinatorics (cs.DS, cs.DM).
